parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the fuel filler pipe or tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially in the engine compartment.
symptoms: Fuel leakage in the engine compartment
fuel leaks from top of filler tube.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire delamination can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The sudden failure of a tire can also cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to steer.
The insufficient length of the seat belts can lead to discomfort, difficulty, or impossibility of wearing the seat belts, compromising the safety of the occupants in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belts are too short
making it difficult or impossible to wear them comfortably
the seat belts do not fit properly
the seat belts cause discomfort or constraint.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Seat Belt Extender Availability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of seat belt extenders can force occupants to compromise on their safety by not wearing the seat belts, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The manufacturer does not provide seat belt extenders
the dealership does not offer seat belt extenders
the occupants are unable to find seat belt extenders compatible with the vehicle.
